WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.940
Your engineers are already running AI agents.

00:00:02.940 --> 00:00:06.680
Gödel's Gate is the runtime security layer
that sees everything they do,

00:00:06.680 --> 00:00:08.780
and decides what they're allowed to do.

00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:14.820
Every action flows from the user, to the agent,
to the data source, and ends in a decision.

00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:16.820
Safe work moves at full speed.

00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:19.280
Risky actions stop before they cause damage.

00:00:19.280 --> 00:00:21.600
Every event is counted and attributed.

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:25.300
Open any event to see the full story:
who initiated it,

00:00:25.300 --> 00:00:28.900
which device was used,
and which agent and model were involved,

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:32.500
along with a threat summary
and a tamper-evident audit trail.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:35.720
Data Authority governs agent execution through trust.

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:40.100
Trusted data becomes context.
Untrusted data does not.

00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:43.500
Only trusted context can change an agent's behavior.

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:47.480
So, a hidden instruction buried inside a webpage or ticket
can be read,

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:49.180
but never obeyed.

00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:51.920
Every alert includes a complete causal chain,

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:54.600
from data origin, to action, to effect.

00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.760
Not a guess. A provable sequence of events.

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:01.440
Apply organization-wide policies
across your entire agent fleet.

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:05.000
Connect once,
and every agent is detected automatically.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:08.320
Gödel's Gate.
Protecting AI agents everywhere they run.
